Subject: [PATCH 2/4] fix[conan]: bundled profiles auto-detect arch and install
 system deps

The sen_gcc and sen_clang profiles in .conan/profiles/ pinned arch=x86_64
and lacked tools.system.package_manager:mode=install. On aarch64 hosts
(Mac M-series Docker, ARM Linux) `--profile=sen_gcc` errored out trying
to apt-install libxext-dev:amd64; on any host without libxext-dev
pre-installed, the conanfile's Apt(self).install() step failed with
"missing but can't install".

Both profiles now resolve arch via {{ detect_api.detect_arch() }} (works
on x86_64 CI runners and on aarch64 dev hosts) and set
tools.system.package_manager:mode=install with sudo=False, matching the
CI image / docker dev container assumption (root, no sudo). Workstation
users override sudo=True or pre-install libxext-dev manually.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .conan/profiles/sen_clang | 10 +++++++++-
 .conan/profiles/sen_gcc   | 10 +++++++++-
 2 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/.conan/profiles/sen_clang b/.conan/profiles/sen_clang
