Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Builds on the original quick installer (a7fc27c) with a substantial
round of UX, correctness, and documentation work:

* Output: brand banner mirroring the term component (6-color block bar),
  pre-install Configuration block, step markers (cyan ▸ in-progress,
  green ✓ done), curl progress bar collapses into a single line via
  cursor manipulation on completion, notes queue flushed as a single
  "Notes" block at the end (so the step column reads as a clean column
  of checkmarks), Enter on the menu picks the line that matches the
  host's compiler.

* Layout fix: LD_LIBRARY_PATH in the activate scripts now points at
  <prefix>/bin to match where Sen actually installs its shared libs
  (CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR per cmake/util/sen_internal_utils.cmake). The
  old <prefix>/lib path was empty. PKG_CONFIG_PATH dropped entirely;
  Sen doesn't generate .pc files.

* '~/.sen/current' symlink: do_install retargets it on every successful
  install, and on the already-installed short-circuit, so a single
  shell-rc line ('. ~/.sen/current/activate') always picks up the
  latest install and 'sh install.sh <old-version>' is a cheap "switch
  back" path.

* Source-file housekeeping: install.sh header trimmed to file identity
  + reading conventions (full reference moved to architecture.md).
  Macos branch removed from conanfile.py:package_info; Darwin case
  removed from host_os(). The bundled installer documentation was
  renamed from README.md to architecture.md (developer-targeted; the
  Sen convention is README.md for user-facing only) and rewritten
  around the install pipeline, env-var contract, security model, and
  test harness rather than duplicating the user docs.

* Tests: bats harness re-enables set -e so every [ ... ] / [[ ... ]]
  is a hard assertion (was silently passing on intermediate misses).
  Two low-value duplicates dropped (parse_toolchain aarch64+clang,
  activate's per-var split tests folded into one). New assertions for
  the symlink behaviour, the env-var contract, and the rollback path.

Tests: 60/60 + 7/7 syntax pass under SEN_DEV_STRICT=1 in the docker
dev container.

