From 42104563adf2a93dd197a15aa4b87b2a5bd64592 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 14:14:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] docs[install]: rewrite install + build guides; remove
 macOS references

* docs/getting_started/install.md restructured around three audiences
  (quick install on Linux, Conan dependency, manual zip extraction).
  The quick-install section is now a 3-step happy path (install,
  activate, check) with details folded into ??? collapsibles. The
  Conan section explicitly leads with 'conan profile detect' and flags
  cmake_find_mode = "none" so users know why find_package(sen) "just
  works" via CMakeDeps. Manual section corrected: LD_LIBRARY_PATH
  points at <prefix>/bin (matches where Sen installs libs), variable
  named SEN_PREFIX (matches the activate script).

* docs/howto_guides/building_from_source.md added (linked from the
  Guides nav). Numbered steps for the Conan-driven path, a 'Common
  first-run errors' table covering the four most likely failures
  (missing default profile, libxext-dev install denied, missing
  --build=missing, compiler-version mismatch), and a 'Matching CI's
  exact toolchain' subsection for the bundled profiles.

* root README.md: a 'curl|sh' one-liner added at the top of Quick
  Start so a github visitor sees the fastest path to try Sen first.
  The CMake-driven snippet drops the redundant
  'source build/.../conanbuild.sh' (the Conan-generated preset already
  embeds the PATH); 'cmake --build build/...' switched to
  'cmake --build --preset conan-gcc-release' to match the rest of the
  docs. Bundled-profiles paragraph mentions 'conan profile detect' as
  the auto-detect alternative.

* docs/components/ether.md: BSD/Darwin sysctl section removed (macOS
  isn't a supported platform).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
